column1: #Text=I know , it ’s almost like it should n’t be possible , yet it is .
#Text=And these guys are thumping their chests about it .
#Text=It ’s like saying you do n’t approve of who and what your daughter is by birth .
#Text=And , again , Cheney is only like six or seven years older than me .
#Text=Like where the f did this shit come from ?
#Text=DS : Has the Iraq War affected you much as a person ?
#Text=I watched the whole Vietnam thing go down and it ’s the exact same thing .
#Text=You think we would learn , but we do n’t because the proof of that is there ’s Holocaust deniers to something that happened a couple years before I was born , that there was extermination .
#Text=Now there ’s people that are n’t sure whether that happened or not , no matter how many shoes are piled up and down in Washington , D.C. .
#Text=Make it appear there are two sides to every fact .
#Text=Yeah , but there ai n't two sides to science .
#Text=And when you start banning science and real knowledge , then you ’re in George Orwell land .
#Text=The pretense of it all really bothers me .
#Text=I hate sitting there , talking to a guy that ’s looking me right in the eye , and he ’s lying to me .
#Text=The only time I want to play pretend is when I can play like a child and not make it into an ideology .
#Text=I know I go way off the subject , but I have a lot to say and a lot of people say , as far as the animation and the celebrities and all that , you know , I ’m not so outspoken .
#Text=Maybe not everybody talks about it , but what am I going to do ?
#Text=DS : Do you think we live in a fear-based society now ?
#Text=It ’s no secret to anybody , unless you fell off a potato truck somewhere .
#Text=DS : What is the reasoning behind questions like , ' Are n’t you afraid of saying such-and-such thing ? '
#Text=Because the person is usually fear-driven himself and totally understands the consequences of telling the truth .
#Text=You do n’t get rewarded for it , let ’s put it that way .
#Text=I ’m optimistic about my own life and things changing for the better .
#Text=I do n’t pin my existence on the industry .
#Text=Some people , without their fame , they would just roll up into a ball and bounce away and I ’m like a reluctant famer , if you know what I mean .
#Text=I do n’t know if I said this .
#Text=I probably already did because I ’ve been talking so long .
#Text=But if you fart the national anthem you can be a celebrity .
#Text=And the idea that the word celebrity and the word diva has been watered down into any girl with a belly button now and some gold chain around her neck can be a diva .
#Text=It does n’t matter why they call the great talents divas , you know women in the theater .

#Text=It ’s like , in my opinion , the guy that can fart the national anthem and is famous is totally equal to someone else who actually has talent and worked their ass off and became famous for having a gift .
#Text=It ’s like you ’re saying there ’s good art and bad art .
